
Intltool does not (yet) know how to find the gettext domain
for packages which do not use autoconf. Thus you have to specify
the domain every time you run intltool-update.
See http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=131114

To regenerate meld.pot:
intltool-update -g meld -p

To update a language:
intltool-update -g meld <lang>

